{
  "texts": [
    "(Gopinath et al. 2018) reported in their research that DT for smart buildings can enhance security by automatically notifying owners and locking doors if an intruder attempts unauthorized access.",
    "Although DT technology has a large number of applications in the building industry, many barriers hinder its widespread adoption.",
    "These barriers include high implementation costs, a lack of standardized data integration methods, a scarcity of skilled professionals, concerns about data security and privacy, and organizational resistance to change.",
    "(Paolo Pileggi 2021) in their position paper, discussed strategies to mitigate the nine barriers related to DT for manufacturing SMEs.",
    "These barriers are consistent with the external and internal barriers discussed in the findings section of our paper."
  ]
}